name: ohio-river-islands-national-wildlife-refuge-annual-narrative-report-fiscal-year-2000-54e41
notes: This annual narrative report for Ohio River Islands National Wildlife Refuge outlines activities and accomplishments during the 2001 fiscal year. The report begins with an introduction to the Refuge. Highlights and weather conditions are summarized for the year. Information about monitoring and studies- including surveys and censuses and studies and investigations- is provided next. Habitat restoration and management projects are also covered; activities include wetland restoration and vegetation control. Fish and wildlife management are discussed next with emphasis on bird banding and nest structures. Coordination activities, such as interagency coordination and private land activities, are outlined. The resource protection section provides an update on law enforcement, permits, contaminants, and land acquisition support. Information about public education and recreation is given including visitor services and outreach. Finally, comprehensive management planning and general administration are discussed in the Refuge planning and administration section.
